1
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,133
[INSECTS BUZZING]

2
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:18,533
MAN, IT'S HOT.

3
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:25,400
WOW, I'D BETTER EAT THIS THING
FAST BEFORE IT MELTS.

4
00:00:27,066 --> 00:00:29,100
[GROANING]

5
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:31,766
ICE POPS IN SUMMER ROCK!

6
00:00:53,866 --> 00:00:57,033
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

7
00:01:00,066 --> 00:01:01,500
HEY, KURO.

8
00:01:05,966 --> 00:01:07,900
[DOOR OPENS]
YOUR TURN.

9
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:10,100
COPY THAT.

10
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:13,300
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT CAT?
HE'S BEEN STANDING THERE
FOR DAYS.

11
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:16,066
WE BRING HIM FOOD,
AND HE DOESN'T
EVEN LOOK AT IT.

12
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:19,666
YEAH, I KNOW.
HE'S A SMART LITTLE GUY.

13
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:23,066
MAYBE HE'S ACTING LIKE THAT
BECAUSE HE'S STARTING TO PUT
TWO AND TWO TOGETHER.

14
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:26,433
HEY, WHAT HAPPENS
TO A FAMILIAR
WHEN ITS MASTER DIES?

15
00:01:26,466 --> 00:01:29,033
I MEAN, HE'S GONNA FIND OUT
AT SOME POINT, YOU KNOW?

16
00:01:29,066 --> 00:01:32,233
SHH. KEEP IT DOWN, DUMMY.
HE'LL HEAR.

17
00:01:32,266 --> 00:01:35,233
RIGHT. SORRY.
HE'S SO FAR AWAY,
I DIDN'T THINK HE'D HEAR ME.

18
00:01:35,266 --> 00:01:40,033
ANYWAY, MY GUESS IS
IT'D BE LIKE LETTING
A DOG OFF ITS LEASH.

19
00:01:40,066 --> 00:01:42,733
HE'LL GO BACK
TO BEING THE DEMON HE WAS.

20
00:01:42,766 --> 00:01:45,566
THEN HE'LL BECOME
A PROBLEM.

21
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:01,200
♪ [MAN SINGING
IN JAPANESE]

22
00:03:35,970 --> 00:03:38,503
[DOOR OPENS]

23
00:03:38,536 --> 00:03:42,270
- OH, YOU'RE BACK.
- EVERYTHING WAS SOLD OUT
AT THE SHOP ON CAMPUS.

24
00:03:42,303 --> 00:03:44,803
I HAD TO GO
TO THE OTHER ONE.

25
00:03:44,836 --> 00:03:47,219
GEEZ, CAN THIS ROOM GET
ANY HOTTER?

26
00:03:47,253 --> 00:03:51,019
I MEAN, IT'S A RICH KIDS'
SCHOOL, SO GET SOME A.C.
UP IN HERE, YOU KNOW?

27
00:03:51,053 --> 00:03:53,720
THIS BUILDING IS REALLY OLD,
SO IT CAN'T BE HELPED.

28
00:03:53,753 --> 00:03:57,953
WE CAN DEAL WITH THIS.
IT'S NOT LIKE WE GREW UP
WITH AIR CONDITIONING ANYWAY.

29
00:03:57,986 --> 00:04:00,386
WE JUST HAVE TO MAKE DO
WITH THE FAN.

30
00:04:00,420 --> 00:04:03,186
I WAS JUST SAYING.
NO, NEVER MIND, RIN.

31
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:06,153
- WHERE'S THE MINERAL WATER
I ASKED FOR?
- HUH?

32
00:04:06,186 --> 00:04:09,420
OH, CRAP. I FORGOT.

33
00:04:09,453 --> 00:04:13,120
I MEAN, WATER.
IT'S TRANSPARENT,
SO IT'S EASY TO MISS.

34
00:04:13,153 --> 00:04:17,220
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU HAVE
AN ICE POP?
NYUM-NYUM.

35
00:04:17,253 --> 00:04:20,253
YOU GOT TWO ICE POPS,
NO WATER.

36
00:04:20,286 --> 00:04:23,386
NO, THANKS.
I'LL GET THE WATER MYSELF
LATER ON.

37
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:26,320
[SIGHS]
FINE. WHATEVER.

38
00:04:26,353 --> 00:04:27,820
[WRAPPER CRACKLING]

39
00:04:37,786 --> 00:04:40,820
[GROANING]

40
00:04:40,853 --> 00:04:46,720
OH, MAN. SPENDING
A SUNDAY AFTERNOON STUCK INDOORS
DOING HOMEWORK TOTALLY SUCKS.

41
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:49,586
AND AFTER ALL I WENT THROUGH
TO MAKE IT TO EXWIRE.

42
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:51,553
THIS AIN'T NO DIFFERENT
THAN BEING A PAGE.

43
00:04:51,586 --> 00:04:55,686
ACCORDING TO THIS HERE CHART,
EXWIRE'S NOTHING
BUT A BOTTOM FEEDER.

44
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:59,886
WHICH ONE OF THESE
IS YOU ANYWAY?

45
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,120
INTERMEDIATE FIRST CLASS.

46
00:05:02,153 --> 00:05:04,553
HMM, INTERMEDIATE FIRST CLASS.

47
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:09,220
THAT'S IT?
GUESS YOU'RE NOT
A HOTSHOT AFTER ALL.

48
00:05:09,253 --> 00:05:11,420
OH, YEAH?
WELL, YOU'RE ONE TO TALK.

49
00:05:11,453 --> 00:05:13,586
HUH?

50
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:16,320
I BET IT TAKES FOREVER
AND A HALF TO GET UP...

51
00:05:16,353 --> 00:05:18,986
TO THIS PALADIN THINGY
AT THE TOP, DOESN'T IT?

52
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:23,353
MAN, I CAN'T WAIT
TO GO ON MISSIONS
AND GET SOME REAL EXPERIENCE.

53
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:29,320
THE RANK OF PALADIN
IS ONLY AWARDED TO ONE
VERY EXCEPTIONAL EXORCIST.

54
00:05:29,353 --> 00:05:32,553
HUH?
THEY DON'T JUST GIVE IT
TO ANYONE, YOU KNOW.

55
00:05:32,586 --> 00:05:36,186
AND NO. WE'RE NOT SENDING YOU
ON ANY MISSIONS ANY TIME SOON.

56
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:38,386
- HUH?
- THAT'S RIGHT.

57
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:40,953
YOU IGNORE ORDERS
AND ACT LIKE A LOOSE CANNON,

58
00:05:40,986 --> 00:05:44,586
NOT TO MENTION
YOU CAN'T EVEN MANAGE
TO RUN A SIMPLE ERRAND.

59
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:47,320
CAN YOU BLAME US?
WHAT THE HELL?
I SAID I'M SORRY.

60
00:05:47,353 --> 00:05:50,420
IT'S NOT JUST THAT.
IT'S THE WAY YOU FIGHT.

61
00:05:50,453 --> 00:05:53,253
YOU RELY TOO MUCH
ON SATAN'S POWER.

62
00:05:53,286 --> 00:05:56,953
DURING A FIGHT, YOU SHOULDN'T BE
SO QUICK TO DRAW YOUR SWORD.

63
00:05:56,986 --> 00:05:59,653
AND IT DOESN'T MATTER
HOW FAST YOU HEAL.

64
00:05:59,686 --> 00:06:03,620
YOU CAN'T KEEP USING
YOUR BODY AS A SHIELD
WHEN YOU RUN OUT OF OPTIONS.

65
00:06:03,653 --> 00:06:07,520
IF YOU KEEP DOING
THINGS LIKE THAT,

66
00:06:07,553 --> 00:06:12,086
WELL, THEN, SATAN'S POWER
WILL COMPLETELY CONSUME YOU.

67
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,886
WHAT? WHO GIVES A DAMN
HOW I DID IT?

68
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,486
IT WORKED,
AND EVERYONE WAS SAFE.

69
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:18,586
YOU SOUND LIKE THE OLD MAN
LECTURING ME.

70
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,520
BESIDES, YOU ALMOST
GOT KILLED TOO.

71
00:06:20,553 --> 00:06:23,153
I'M TELLING YOU THIS
BECAUSE I WANT TO HELP YOU.

72
00:06:23,186 --> 00:06:25,120
DAD WOULD WANT THE SAME THING.

73
00:06:25,153 --> 00:06:28,120
I'D IMAGINE HE'S SPINNING
IN HIS GRAVE RIGHT NOW
WORRYING ABOUT YOU.

74
00:06:28,153 --> 00:06:32,186
YEAH, RIGHT.
LIKE THAT OLD FART EVER CARED
THAT MUCH ABOUT ANYTHING I DID.

75
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:33,786
OLD FART, HUH?

76
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:36,720
WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO STOP ACTING LIKE
SOME REBELLIOUS TEENAGER?

77
00:06:36,753 --> 00:06:38,853
DON'T YOU THINK
IT'S ABOUT TIME
YOU GREW UP?

78
00:06:38,886 --> 00:06:42,020
OH, YEAH?
WELL, WHEN ARE YOU GONNA STOP
ACTING LIKE SOME BIG SHOT?

79
00:06:42,053 --> 00:06:44,620
WALKING AROUND LIKE YOU'RE
THE MAN 'CAUSE YOU'RE
ALL BRAINY AND STUFF.

80
00:06:44,653 --> 00:06:47,820
- AND SHIEMI'S
CRUSHING ON YOU.
- HUH?

81
00:06:47,853 --> 00:06:50,920
WHAT DOES SHIEMI HAVE TO DO
WITH ANYTHING I'M TALKING ABOUT?

82
00:06:50,953 --> 00:06:54,853
BESIDES, SHE'S NOT CRUSHING
ON ME, AND I DO NOT WALK AROUND
LIKE I'M THE MAN.

83
00:06:54,886 --> 00:06:56,786
OH, MY GOD!
SHE TOTALLY IS.

84
00:06:56,820 --> 00:07:00,020
YOU'VE GOT FOUR EYES, FOUR-EYES.
HOW COME YOU CAN'T SEE THAT?

85
00:07:00,053 --> 00:07:02,186
YOU'VE GOTTA BE
ONE HELL OF A MORON.

86
00:07:02,220 --> 00:07:03,986
I AM A MORON, HUH?

87
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,820
I WONDER WHAT
THAT MAKES YOU THEN,

88
00:07:05,853 --> 00:07:08,420
SEEING AS HOW
YOU CAN'T EVEN RUN
A SIMPLE ERRAND.

89
00:07:08,453 --> 00:07:11,853
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE STILL WHINING ABOUT THAT.

90
00:07:11,886 --> 00:07:16,353
YOUR FIGHTING IS SLOPPY.
YOU USE BRUTE FORCE BECAUSE
YOU LACK KNOWLEDGE AND SKILL.

91
00:07:16,386 --> 00:07:18,253
WHY DON'T YOU TRY USING
YOUR HEAD FOR A CHANGE?

92
00:07:18,286 --> 00:07:19,720
FOUR-EYED PIECE OF CRAP!

93
00:07:30,953 --> 00:07:33,153
[LAUGHS]

94
00:07:33,186 --> 00:07:36,420
LOOK AT THAT.
THEY LANDED PERFECTLY.

95
00:07:36,453 --> 00:07:40,186
WHAT IN THE HELL
IS SO FREAKING FUNNY?

96
00:07:40,220 --> 00:07:42,720
- [GASPS]
- [VIBRATES]

97
00:07:46,886 --> 00:07:48,953
OKUMURA SPEAKING.

98
00:07:48,986 --> 00:07:51,720
RIGHT.
I'M ON MY WAY NOW.

99
00:07:51,753 --> 00:07:53,620
IS THAT A MISSION?

100
00:07:53,653 --> 00:07:56,720
IT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.
[GROWLS]

101
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,620
HE'S GOT A BUTTLOAD OF SPARES.

102
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:07,853
[CAT HISSES, SNARLS]

103
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:16,020
YUKIO OKUMURA,
INTERMEDIATE EXORCIST
FIRST CLASS.

104
00:08:16,053 --> 00:08:17,553
WE'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.

105
00:08:17,586 --> 00:08:20,420
AND I'M RIN OKUMURA, EXWIRE.
NO CLASS.

106
00:08:20,453 --> 00:08:22,853
UH-UH. YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE.

107
00:08:22,886 --> 00:08:25,286
JUST MAKING SURE YOU DON'T BREAK
YOUR SECOND PAIR OF GLASSES.

108
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:29,120
WHAT ARE YOU, CRAZY?
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO PLAY
THESE GAMES OF YOURS RIGHT NOW.

109
00:08:29,153 --> 00:08:31,286
- GO AWAY.
- TOUGH SHIT.

110
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,553
[LAUGHS]
[HISSING, SNARLING]

111
00:08:33,586 --> 00:08:36,353
THIS WAY, PLEASE.
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT FOR ME?

112
00:08:36,386 --> 00:08:39,620
KURO THE CAT SI THAT GUARDS
THE SOUTH GATE HAS GONE BERSERK.

113
00:08:39,653 --> 00:08:42,920
WE'VE SET UP A PERIMETER
AND LOCKED DOWN
THE REAR GATE ROAD.

114
00:08:42,953 --> 00:08:44,720
[HISSING]

115
00:08:51,886 --> 00:08:54,120
[KURO]
YOU LIARS!

116
00:08:54,153 --> 00:08:56,520
YOU'RE ALL LIARS!

117
00:08:56,553 --> 00:08:59,353
[YUKIO]
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

118
00:08:59,386 --> 00:09:02,786
KURO SUDDENLY
GREW BIG LIKE THAT,
THEN HE ATTACKED US.

119
00:09:02,820 --> 00:09:05,786
WE WERE TALKING,
AND I GUESS WE SORT
OF LET IT SLIP...

120
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,786
THAT FATHER FUJIMOTO
HAD DIED.

121
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:09,986
AND, WELL,
I THINK HE HEARD US.

122
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:14,820
I'M SORRY.
EXCUSE ME, I WAS WONDERING
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO KURO.

123
00:09:14,853 --> 00:09:18,886
DON'T WORRY.
WE EXORCISTS
ARE GOING TO TAKE HIM DOWN.

124
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,553
SERIOUSLY?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

125
00:09:21,586 --> 00:09:25,186
WHAT DOES THAT CAT
OR ANY OF THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH THE OLD MAN'S DEATH?

126
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:30,053
THAT CAT IS CALLED A CAT SI.
IT WAS DAD'S FAMILIAR.

127
00:09:30,086 --> 00:09:33,653
YOU'RE KIDDING.
WHAT THE HELL'S
A CAT SI ANYWAY?

128
00:09:33,686 --> 00:09:36,386
A DEMON THAT POSSESSES CATS.

129
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:39,720
THE ONES IN JAPAN ARE UNIQUE,
BECAUSE IF THEY LIVE
LONG ENOUGH,

130
00:09:39,753 --> 00:09:41,853
THEY DEVELOP THAT SPLIT TAIL.

131
00:09:41,886 --> 00:09:46,286
THIS PARTICULAR ONE USED TO LIVE
IN A PART OF THE COUNTRY
THAT CULTIVATED SILK,

132
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,986
AND FOR CENTURIES HE WAS
THE GUARDIAN DEITY OF SILKWORMS.

133
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:51,753
HE LIVED PEACEFULLY
AMONG HUMANS,

134
00:09:51,786 --> 00:09:54,686
AND PROTECTED SILKWORMS
FROM MICE AND OTHER PREDATORS.

135
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,486
THE PEOPLE OF THE COMMUNITY
WORSHIPPED HIM IN THEIR SHRINE.

136
00:10:01,786 --> 00:10:05,186
BUT AS THE TIMES CHANGED
AND SILKWORM BREEDING DIED OUT,

137
00:10:06,953 --> 00:10:11,386
THE PEOPLE FORGOT
ABOUT THEIR GUARDIAN
AND ALL HE'D DONE FOR THEM.

138
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,186
AND THEN--

139
00:10:21,927 --> 00:10:26,294
HAVING LOST HIS HOME,
HE BECAME A DEMON.

140
00:10:26,327 --> 00:10:28,661
[SNARLING]

141
00:10:37,461 --> 00:10:38,794
NOW!
RIGHT.

142
00:10:43,927 --> 00:10:46,927
- [SNARLS]
- OH, CRAP.
IT DIDN'T WORK.

143
00:10:55,727 --> 00:10:58,194
LIARS!

144
00:10:58,227 --> 00:11:01,061
YOU'RE ALL LIARS!

145
00:11:02,327 --> 00:11:04,027
LIARS!

146
00:11:16,039 --> 00:11:17,972
[HISSING, SNARLING]

147
00:11:20,406 --> 00:11:21,639
[SHOUTING]

148
00:11:32,539 --> 00:11:34,906
[SNARLING]

149
00:11:34,939 --> 00:11:37,339
WHAT'S THE SITUATION?
OKUMURA?

150
00:11:37,372 --> 00:11:41,306
WE TRIED HOLY WATER,
HOLY WINE, SILVER, HERBS--
NOTHING'S WORKING.

151
00:11:41,339 --> 00:11:44,039
WE CAN'T USE AN ARIA ON IT
BECAUSE WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE...

152
00:11:44,072 --> 00:11:46,539
TO FIGURE OUT WHAT ITS
FATAL VERSE IS YET.

153
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:48,839
WE PUMPED HIM FULL
OF TRANQUILIZERS,
SO HE'S WEAK.

154
00:11:48,872 --> 00:11:50,939
HE'LL SNAP OUT OF IT
SOON THOUGH.

155
00:11:50,972 --> 00:11:53,206
GOD HELP US WHEN HE DOES.

156
00:11:53,239 --> 00:11:55,206
[GROWLING]

157
00:11:57,306 --> 00:12:00,406
DID FATHER FUJIMOTO EVER TELL
YOU ANYTHING ABOUT KURO?

158
00:12:00,439 --> 00:12:03,806
YUKIO, REMEMBER
A COUPLE OF YEARS AGO
WHEN WE WENT ON THAT MISSION?

159
00:12:03,839 --> 00:12:06,006
YES.
WHAT MISSION?

160
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:09,372
HUH?
IT WAS BACK WHEN YUKIO
WAS STILL AN EXWIRE.

161
00:12:09,406 --> 00:12:12,972
A SERIES OF UNEXPLAINED
PHENOMENA WERE REPORTED...

162
00:12:13,006 --> 00:12:14,639
AT A CONSTRUCTION SITE.

163
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:21,372
[SHOUTING]

164
00:12:25,272 --> 00:12:26,606
[SCREECHING]

165
00:12:28,472 --> 00:12:33,106
THE LOCALS THOUGHT IT WAS
A CURSE, SO THEY BROUGHT IN
SOME SHAMAN TO HELP,

166
00:12:33,139 --> 00:12:35,906
BUT THEY WERE NO MATCH
FOR THE CAT SI.

167
00:12:35,939 --> 00:12:38,639
THEN THINGS GOT WORSE.

168
00:12:38,672 --> 00:12:43,006
OUT OF OPTIONS,
THE LOCALS CALLED IN THE
KNIGHTS OF THE TRUE CROSS...

169
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:44,539
AS A LAST RESORT.

170
00:12:44,572 --> 00:12:48,239
THE MAN WHO WAS SUPPOSED
TO DESTROY THE DEMON...

171
00:12:48,272 --> 00:12:51,706
WAS FATHER FUJIMOTO,
THE PALADIN.

172
00:12:51,739 --> 00:12:52,806
[GASPS]

173
00:12:52,839 --> 00:12:54,706
I THINK I CAN HANDLE...

174
00:12:54,739 --> 00:12:57,639
THIS LITTLE FUR BALL
ON MY OWN.

175
00:13:06,639 --> 00:13:10,006
HE RESOLVED THE SITUATION
WITHOUT RESORTING TO VIOLENCE.

176
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,572
HE WAS AMAZING.

177
00:13:12,739 --> 00:13:15,872
THE OLD FART WAS A PALADIN?

178
00:13:15,906 --> 00:13:17,806
GEEZ, I HAD NO IDEA.

179
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:21,206
AFTER THAT, DAD NAMED HIM KURO
AND MADE A CONTRACT WITH HIM...

180
00:13:21,239 --> 00:13:24,039
TO BE THE ACADEMY'S
RESIDENT GATE KEEPER.

181
00:13:25,272 --> 00:13:27,372
ONCE A DEMON, ALWAYS A DEMON.

182
00:13:27,406 --> 00:13:30,972
AS SOON AS HE LOSES HIS MASTER,
HE REVERTS BACK
TO HIS NATURAL HABITS.

183
00:13:31,006 --> 00:13:35,539
MY FATHER SUSPECTED
THIS WOULD HAPPEN SOMEDAY,
SO HE PREPARED THIS.

184
00:13:35,572 --> 00:13:39,906
IF ANYTHING EVER HAPPENS TO ME
AND KURO BECOMES UNMANAGEABLE,

185
00:13:39,939 --> 00:13:42,439
I WANT YOU TO USE THIS
TO STOP HIM.

186
00:13:42,472 --> 00:13:45,206
IT'S SOMETHING I WHIPPED UP
ESPECIALLY FOR THAT.

187
00:13:45,239 --> 00:13:48,206
USE IT AND HE WILL BE AT PEACE.

188
00:13:48,239 --> 00:13:51,606
IT SEEMS TO BE
A MODIFIED HAND GRENADE.

189
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:55,606
I SUPPOSE IT'S FILLED
WITH SOME MEDICINE
THAT WILL KILL HIM.

190
00:13:55,639 --> 00:13:56,939
LET'S HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

191
00:13:56,972 --> 00:13:58,772
LISTEN UP, EVERYONE.

192
00:13:58,806 --> 00:14:00,639
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THIS THING
IS CAPABLE OF,

193
00:14:00,672 --> 00:14:03,872
SO I HAVE TO ASK ALL OF YOU
TO STEP BACK AND LET ME
HANDLE THIS ALONE.

194
00:14:03,906 --> 00:14:06,439
[KURO]
YOU LIARS!

195
00:14:06,472 --> 00:14:08,106
LIARS!

196
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:11,006
SHIRO IS THE MOST POWERFUL
ONE OF ALL!

197
00:14:12,539 --> 00:14:13,939
[WOMAN]
YOU SURE?

198
00:14:13,972 --> 00:14:16,906
[YUKIO] I'LL BE FINE.
I JUST HAVE TO HIT HIM
WITH IT AND IT'S DONE.

199
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:21,339
I'M GOING TO EVACUATE EVERYONE
IN CASE THAT THING TURNS OUT
TO BE NASTY.

200
00:14:21,372 --> 00:14:23,606
RETREAT TO THE REAR GATE,
PEOPLE.

201
00:14:26,839 --> 00:14:30,339
[SNARLING]
SHIRO WOULD NEVER DIE!

202
00:14:30,372 --> 00:14:33,372
SHIRO WILL COME BACK.

203
00:14:33,406 --> 00:14:36,239
HE'S COMING BACK!

204
00:14:38,706 --> 00:14:40,706
OH, THAT'S IT.

205
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:45,962
OKAY. YOU'D BETTER GET BACK.

206
00:14:45,996 --> 00:14:47,862
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THIS MEDICINE'S LIKE,

207
00:14:47,896 --> 00:14:49,996
AND IT MIGHT HAVE AN EFFECT
ON YOU TOO.

208
00:14:50,029 --> 00:14:52,429
ARE YOU GONNA KILL HIM?

209
00:14:52,462 --> 00:14:55,996
YEAH. THIS SCHOOL DOESN'T HAVE
AN EXORCIST ON THE FACULTY...

210
00:14:56,029 --> 00:14:57,962
WHO CAN TAME A DEMON
OF THAT CLASS.

211
00:14:59,162 --> 00:15:01,929
THE WAY HE IS,
OUR ONLY OPTION
IS TO KILL HIM.

212
00:15:01,962 --> 00:15:03,596
[GROWLING]

213
00:15:03,629 --> 00:15:05,862
SHIRO IS COMING BACK.

214
00:15:05,896 --> 00:15:09,196
AND UNTIL HE DOES,
I'M NOT GOING TO DIE.

215
00:15:12,196 --> 00:15:14,196
GO ON, RIN.
TIME TO GET BACK.

216
00:15:15,362 --> 00:15:17,129
HOLD UP.
WHAT?

217
00:15:17,162 --> 00:15:19,862
WELL, ISN'T KILLING HIM
KIND OF EXTREME?

218
00:15:19,896 --> 00:15:21,629
I THINK HE JUST
MIGHT BE SAD, IS ALL.

219
00:15:23,129 --> 00:15:26,396
- HOW WOULD YOU KNOW THAT?
- MM, I DON'T KNOW HOW I KNOW.

220
00:15:26,429 --> 00:15:30,462
IT'S-- IT'S KINDA LIKE
DEMON-TO-DEMON TELEPATHY.

221
00:15:30,496 --> 00:15:34,696
HMM. EVEN IF YOU'RE RIGHT,
WE CAN'T JUST LEAVE HIM
LIKE THIS.

222
00:15:34,729 --> 00:15:37,929
THEN GIVE ME A MINUTE TO TRY
TO TALK SOME SENSE INTO HIM.

223
00:15:37,962 --> 00:15:40,362
TALK SOME SENSE?
YEAH. DON'T WORRY.

224
00:15:40,396 --> 00:15:43,296
I WON'T DRAW MY SWORD.
I'LL DO WHAT YOU SAID.

225
00:15:43,329 --> 00:15:47,262
I WON'T USE SATAN'S POWER.
I'M GONNA USE MY HEAD
TO FIGHT HIM INSTEAD.

226
00:15:47,296 --> 00:15:48,596
HUH?

227
00:16:00,929 --> 00:16:02,696
HEY!
DON'T YELL!

228
00:16:02,729 --> 00:16:04,729
[SNARLS]

229
00:16:04,762 --> 00:16:08,562
MY NAME'S RIN OKUMURA.
I'M SHIRO'S SON.

230
00:16:08,596 --> 00:16:11,362
SHIRO'S--

231
00:16:11,396 --> 00:16:14,196
MY FATHER'S DEAD.

232
00:16:15,562 --> 00:16:18,362
WAIT, RIN.
SHIRO'S DEAD.

233
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:23,429
THAT'S A LIE.
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU!

234
00:16:23,462 --> 00:16:26,129
- SHIRO'S DEAD!
- <i>LIAR!</i>

235
00:16:26,162 --> 00:16:29,162
[ROARS]
<i>STOP LYING TO ME!</i>

236
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:38,162
WHAT?

237
00:16:38,196 --> 00:16:40,596
HE ACTUALLY USED HIS HEAD?

238
00:16:40,629 --> 00:16:42,196
[GROANING]

239
00:16:46,796 --> 00:16:48,129
[SNIFFS]

240
00:16:51,762 --> 00:16:53,929
HUH?

241
00:16:53,962 --> 00:16:57,596
IT'S OKAY.
I BET YOU REALLY LOVED MY DAD,
DIDN'T YOU?

242
00:16:57,629 --> 00:16:59,462
[GASPS]

243
00:16:59,496 --> 00:17:04,296
THOUGHT SO.
AND ALL THIS, IT'S JUST BECAUSE
YOU'RE SAD, ISN'T IT?

244
00:17:07,162 --> 00:17:11,062
KNOW WHAT?
I'M SAD ABOUT IT TOO.

245
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:13,262
SO HOW ABOUT
WE BE FRIENDS?

246
00:17:19,762 --> 00:17:22,062
RIN.

247
00:17:27,596 --> 00:17:32,229
IT'S OKAY.
YOU REALLY LOVED HUMANS,
DIDN'T YOU?

248
00:17:32,262 --> 00:17:35,962
AND ALL THIS, IT'S ALL
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE SAD...

249
00:17:35,996 --> 00:17:38,229
THAT THEY FORGOT
ABOUT YOU, ISN'T IT, HUH?

250
00:17:38,262 --> 00:17:39,962
[MEOWS]

251
00:17:43,129 --> 00:17:47,929
SO HOW ABOUT WE BE FRIENDS.
LOOK. I EVEN MADE YOU
SOME SILVER VINE SAKE.

252
00:17:47,962 --> 00:17:50,462
[CONTENTED MEWLING]

253
00:17:59,396 --> 00:18:02,196
[MEWLING]

254
00:18:02,229 --> 00:18:03,729
SHIRO.

255
00:18:03,762 --> 00:18:06,129
[LAUGHING]

256
00:18:10,329 --> 00:18:12,296
SHIRO!

257
00:18:12,329 --> 00:18:13,929
[LAUGHING]

258
00:18:17,996 --> 00:18:20,529
CAN'T I SEE YOU AGAIN?

259
00:18:20,562 --> 00:18:21,796
SHIRO?

260
00:18:21,829 --> 00:18:23,929
[MEOWING]

261
00:18:27,629 --> 00:18:29,629
ARE YOU REALLY DEAD?

262
00:18:39,629 --> 00:18:41,196
[MEOWING]

263
00:18:48,096 --> 00:18:50,562
[MEOWING CONTINUES]

264
00:18:57,196 --> 00:18:59,696
HUH.

265
00:18:59,729 --> 00:19:02,396
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF RIN OKUMURA?

266
00:19:02,429 --> 00:19:05,329
AT THIS POINT,
I DON'T HAVE MUCH TO GO ON.

267
00:19:05,362 --> 00:19:08,462
BESIDES, I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM
GO ALL OUT IN BATTLE YET.

268
00:19:08,496 --> 00:19:12,196
I KNOW.
HE'S BEEN CONSISTENT
IN THAT KIND OF BEHAVIOR.

269
00:19:12,229 --> 00:19:14,462
RATHER EXASPERATING
IS WHAT IT IS.

270
00:19:14,496 --> 00:19:18,029
WELL, WOULD YOU LIKE TO TRY
ENTICING HIM INTO GOING ALL OUT?

271
00:19:18,062 --> 00:19:22,429
YES. BUT BEFORE I DO,
I THINK I'LL TRY
TO LEARN MORE...

272
00:19:22,462 --> 00:19:25,462
ABOUT THIS JAPAN PLACE
WHICH YOU SEEM TO BE SO FOND OF.

273
00:19:25,496 --> 00:19:28,496
OH. COLOR ME IMPRESSED.

274
00:19:28,529 --> 00:19:31,829
JUST SO WE'RE CLEAR,
I DID NOT GIVE YOU
THE INFINITY KEY...

275
00:19:31,862 --> 00:19:34,162
SO YOU COULD GO
SIGHTSEEING.

276
00:19:34,196 --> 00:19:36,662
SURE.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

277
00:19:36,696 --> 00:19:38,429
[DOOR CLOSES]

278
00:19:40,796 --> 00:19:42,596
ARE YOU SURE
WE CAN TRUST HIM?

279
00:19:42,629 --> 00:19:44,296
OH, SURE.
HE'LL BE FINE.

280
00:19:44,329 --> 00:19:48,096
I'VE-- HOW DO YOU SAY--
PIQUED HIS INTEREST.

281
00:19:52,062 --> 00:19:54,329
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

282
00:20:00,229 --> 00:20:01,962
[PURRING]

283
00:20:07,029 --> 00:20:09,062
[YUKIO]
SORRY I'M LATE.

284
00:20:09,096 --> 00:20:10,629
HEY.

285
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:15,962
- HE LIKES YOU.
- [MEOWS]

286
00:20:15,996 --> 00:20:17,562
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO HIM?

287
00:20:17,596 --> 00:20:20,729
OH, WELL, I TOLD HIM
THAT HE'S BECOME YOUR FAMILIAR.

288
00:20:20,762 --> 00:20:22,762
A RATHER CLEVER EXCUSE,
IF I MIGHT SAY.

289
00:20:22,796 --> 00:20:27,596
THEY'RE GOING TO USE A DIFFERENT
FAMILIAR TO GUARD THE REAR
SOUTH GATE NOW.

290
00:20:27,629 --> 00:20:29,462
[MEOWS]

291
00:20:29,496 --> 00:20:34,296
- NO, THAT'S POISON!
- <i>HEY, THIS SMELLS LIKE</i>
<i>A PRESENT FROM SHIRO.</i>

292
00:20:34,329 --> 00:20:38,329
UH, HE SAYS THAT THING SMELLS
LIKE A PRESENT FROM THE OLD MAN.

293
00:20:47,196 --> 00:20:48,896
[SNIFFS]

294
00:20:48,929 --> 00:20:51,029
THIS IS SILVER VINE SAKE.

295
00:20:51,062 --> 00:20:54,929
SILVER VINE SAKE!
IT'S SHIRO'S SILVER VINE SAKE!

296
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:58,529
LET ME HAVE IT!
OH, LET ME HAVE MY PRESENT!

297
00:20:58,562 --> 00:21:02,029
[LAUGHING]

298
00:21:02,062 --> 00:21:03,962
WHAT'S UP WITH YOU?

299
00:21:03,996 --> 00:21:08,829
I JUST REALIZED THERE'S
ABSOLUTELY NO WAY DAD WOULD
EVER WANT TO KILL KURO.

300
00:21:08,862 --> 00:21:10,962
[MEOWS]

301
00:21:13,696 --> 00:21:15,229
[SIGHS]

302
00:21:25,429 --> 00:21:29,762
YOU KNOW, OUR OLD MAN
WAS ACTUALLY PRETTY AWESOME.

303
00:21:29,796 --> 00:21:31,696
HUH?
[GASPS]

304
00:21:31,729 --> 00:21:34,196
NOTHING.
I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

305
00:21:36,696 --> 00:21:38,596
YUMMY!

306
00:21:42,962 --> 00:21:44,329
[MEOWS]

307
00:21:51,329 --> 00:21:54,329
♪ [MAN SINGING IN JAPANESE]

308
00:23:18,362 --> 00:23:20,562
[MEWLING]

309
00:23:22,362 --> 00:23:24,729
HOW ABOUT A TOAST?

310
00:23:24,762 --> 00:23:26,496
TO KURO AND THE OLD MAN.

311
00:23:26,529 --> 00:23:29,829
YOU'D BETTER NOT, RIN.
HUMANS SHOULDN'T BE DRINKING
THAT STUFF.

312
00:23:29,862 --> 00:23:32,896
OH, COME ON, MAN.
IT'S JUST FOR SHOW.

313
00:23:32,929 --> 00:23:35,062
YOU KNOW,
TO MARK THE OCCASION.

314
00:23:37,096 --> 00:23:39,962
OKAY. BUT JUST FOR SHOW.

315
00:23:42,062 --> 00:23:44,362
ALL RIGHT, BOTTOMS UP.

316
00:23:44,396 --> 00:23:45,496
BOTTOMS UP.

317
00:23:47,096 --> 00:23:50,229
- IDIOT!
- [GROANS]

318
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:51,662
GROSS.

319
00:23:51,696 --> 00:23:57,162
[SIGHS]
SHIRO'S SILVER VINE SAKE.

320
00:23:57,196 --> 00:23:59,162
YUM, YUM.

321
00:24:03,062 --> 00:24:05,896
[RIN]
SUMMERTIME.
THE OCEAN.

322
00:24:05,929 --> 00:24:07,462
[SHIMA]
THE BIKINIS!

323
00:24:07,496 --> 00:24:09,129
LET'S HIT ON CHICKS!

324
00:24:09,162 --> 00:24:13,596
OH, MAN, I LOVE THE OCEAN!

